TODO defaults for all actions

DOCKET DATA TO ADD TO THE DST SHIP (kad cu pisat readme)
#docket-data=[title='App Store' info='A tool for decentralized curation and discovery of Urbit apps' color=0x1231 version=[0 0 1] website='https://github.com/dilryd-mopreg/app-store' license='MIT' base=%app-store image='some-link']

CONVENIENCE STUFF IN DOJO
=data -build-file /=app-store=/sur/app-store/data/hoon

=some-app :*
    description='some description 1'
    keywords=`keywords:data`~[%keyword1 %keyword2]
    screenshots=`screenshots:data`~['screen1' 'screen2']
    dst-desk='~des/app1'
==
 - note - it's important to make sure that dst-desk is written correctly

DEV ACTIONS

:dev-server|add %app1 some-app
:dev-server|edit %app1 some-app
:dev-server|del %app1

DST ACTIONS

:dst-server|sign [~dev %app1]
:dst-server|send-data [~dev %app1]

CUR ACTIONS

:cur-server|sub ~dev
:cur-server|unsub ~dev
:cur-server|cur-info ['Title' 'image link' 'Intro text']
:cur-server|cats (silt `(list @tas)`~[%cat1 %cat2])
:cur-server|select ~[[~dev %app1]] (malt (limo ~[[[~dev %app1] %cat1]]))

USR ACTIONS

:usr-server|sub ~ter
:usr-server|unsub ~ter

VISIT-DEV ACTIONS

:usr-server|rate [~dev %app1] 5
:usr-server|unrate [~dev %app1]
:usr-server|add-com [~dev %app1] 'this app is great'
:usr-server|edit-com [~dev %app1] ~2022.11.30..00.15.20..cd08 'this app is not that good after all'
:usr-server|del-com [~dev %app1] ~2022.11.30..00.15.20..cd08
:usr-server|put-rev [~dev %app1] 'this app is not malicious' 0v123 %.y
:usr-server|del-rev [~dev %app1]

 - note - insert the exact timestamp of the comment you want to edit/delete,
          since comments are keyed by timestamp
        - the hash inputted in the review is compared to the hash in the app-page
          to ensure that the correct version of the app has been reviewed. this
          is visible in the is-current value in a review
